ADT
ADT - Abstract datatype
ADT is type for objects whose behaviour is described by a set of values and operations

Difference between interface and implementation 
interface :
interface defines what an object can do
implementation:
implementation carries out the instruction defined in the interface

control structures :
the program that causes jump of control from one part of the program to another
types of control structures:
1.sequential statement
2.alternative or branching statement
3.looping or iterative statement
